{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646307","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646307"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:28:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:28:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18170"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18170","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18170"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.3,0.1,0.2,0.25,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10884"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114022"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10884","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10884"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18170"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96037"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7302"},{"type":"tags","id":"7310"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25314"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25317"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114022","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114022"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following thoracic vertebrae has one whole facet and one demifacet for rib articulation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["T1","T2","T9","T10","T11"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe thoracic vertebrae are characterised by their articulation with ribs. Each thoracic vertebra has specific facets or demifacets for rib attachment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003ET1\u003C/strong\u003E vertebra has one whole facet and one demifacet. The whole facet articulates with the first rib, while the demifacet articulates with the second rib. This unique configuration distinguishes T1 from other thoracic vertebrae.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ET2\u003C/strong\u003E has two demifacets for articulation with the second and third ribs. \u003Cstrong\u003ET9\u003C/strong\u003E usually has two demifacets for articulation with the ninth and tenth ribs. \u003Cstrong\u003ET10\u003C/strong\u003E often has a single whole facet for articulation with the tenth rib, whilst \u003Cstrong\u003ET11\u003C/strong\u003E has a single whole facet for articulation with the eleventh rib.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The T1 vertebra has one whole facet and one demifacet for rib articulation.","Thoracic vertebrae have facets and demifacets for articulation with ribs.","The T1 vertebra articulates with the first and second ribs."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Henson B, Kadiyala B, Edens MA. Anatomy, Back, Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537074/","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Rockwood, C. A., Wirth, M. A., \u0026 Fehringer, E. V. (2016). Rockwood and Matsen\u0027s The Shoulder E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","DeSai C, Reddy V, Agarwal A. Anatomy, Back, Vertebral Column. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK525969/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96037"}},"question"